patch available.

  - In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved: crypto: qat - resolve race condition
    during AER recovery During the PCI AER system's error recovery process, the kernel driver may encounter a
    race condition with freeing the reset_data structure's memory. If the device restart will take more than
    10 seconds the function scheduling that restart will exit due to a timeout, and the reset_data structure
    will be freed. However, this data structure is used for completion notification after the restart is
    completed, which leads to a UAF bug. This results in a KFENCE bug notice. BUG: KFENCE: use-after-free read
    in adf_device_reset_worker+0x38/0xa0 [intel_qat] Use-after-free read at 0x00000000bc56fddf (in
    kfence-#142): adf_device_reset_worker+0x38/0xa0 [intel_qat] process_one_work+0x173/0x340 To resolve this
    race condition, the memory associated to the container of the work_struct is freed on the worker if the
    timeout expired, otherwise on the function that schedules the worker. The timeout detection can be done by
    checking if the caller is still waiting for completion or not by using completion_done() function.
    (CVE-2024-26974)

Note that Nessus relies on the presence of the package as reported by the vendor.");
